==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suavity
<hw>Suav"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>suavitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>suavit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Sweetness to the taste.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The quality of being sweet or pleasing to the mind;
agreeableness; softness; pleasantness; gentleness; urbanity; <as>as,
<ex>suavity</ex> of manners; <ex>suavity</ex> of language, conversation,
or address</as>.</def> <rj><au>Glanvill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sub-</ent>⟦br⟧
